*UPDATES AND PATCHES* April 4th, 2018
[Error codes and Severity codes] ================================ [05] Exception/Normal. [00] SUCCESS! [02] FAILURE! [01] Unknown Event. [03] Exception/ Event unknown. [04] Failure but system completed task. ================================
Severity Codes/Levels ============================================= [001] Minor Exception: severity level 10 [002] Minor/medium Exception: severity level 20-30 [003] Medium Exception: severity level 40 [004] Medium/major Exception: severity level 50-60 [005] Major Exception: severity level 70 [006] Major/High Exception: severity level 80 [007] High Exception: severity level 90 [008] Urgent Exception: severity level 100 [009] Network Problem: 0 severity level [010] Unknown Problem: Requires Debugging
These codes are used to define the exceptions you get in the log file if you have trouble finding out what they mean refer to this information.
[04] you will encounter this error many times it more than likely will be the most common one this refers to a problem with programming and it is not on the users side so dont worry about it.
[05] this means an exception was caught and the problem was fixed and not in the slightest of importance its just for my reference.
_____________________________________________
*UPDATES AND PATCHES* April 3rd, 2018
*PLEASE READ CAREFULLY*
Today is the first day where i start implementing logging so i can better debug and find errors related to the program that is not always displayed keep in mind this logging is recording what options you use in sedt so if an error rises then i can find out what option(s) you used leading up to the error. You will be able to disable this, doing so will attempt a deletion on startup and exit of the "log.dat" file
I highly encorage to keep the logging enabled so if something does happen you can send me the log file and i can figure out whats going on, or what error occured.
I CANNOT OBTAIN THE LOG FILE ON MY OWN I NEED YOU TO SEND IT TO ME IF YOU REQUIRE ASSITANCE.
